I - SYNTAX

  a - Command
      - COMMAND_NAME  : arg1 , arg2...          / return values

  b - Arguments
     !   = Not mandatory
    { }  = Array of size 1 to x
     |   = "or"

  c- Command size (octets)

  [Command][len_arg][arguments]
      4        4        ...

II - COMMANDS

  a - Client to server:
      1   - CONNECT       : Name, Pass              / 200 (true) - 4xx
      2   - REGISTER      : Name, Pass              / 200 (true) - 4xx
      3   - UPDATE        : Name, TYPE, new, old    / 200 (true) - 4xx
      4   - ADD           : Name                    / 180 (wait)
      5   - DELETE        : Name                    / 180 (wait)
      6   - STATUS        : status                  / 200 (true) - 4xx
      7   - JOIN          : client | channel        / 200 (true) - 4xx
      8   - LEAVE         : client | channel        / 200 (true) - 4xx
      9   - CALL          : client | channel        / 200 (true) - 4xx
      10  - CANCEL        : client
      11  - LIST_FRIENDS  : !{FRIENDS, ...}         /
      12  - LIST_CHANNELS : !{CHANNELS, ...}        / 
      13  - SEND          : Name | Channel, MESSAGE
      19  - PONG          : Key
      20  - DISCONNECT
      21  - QUIT

  b - Server to client :
      3   - UPDATE        : Name, TYPE, new, old    / 200 (true) - 4xx
      4   - ADD           : Name                    / OK - KO
      5   - DELETE        : Name                    / 180 (wait)
      6   - STATUS        : Name, status
      7   - JOIN          : client | channel, client
      8   - LEAVE         : client | channel, client/ 200 (true) - 4xx
      9   - CALL          : Name                    / 200 (true) - 4xx
      10  - CANCEL        : client
      13  - SEND          : client | channel, client, MESSAGE
      18  - PING          : Key
      100 - Wait
      180 - Ringing
      200 - Ok
      201 - Friend informations
      202 - Channel informations
      203 - End of list
      204 - Successfull call : port
      301 - Not enough argument
      302 - Too many argument
      303 - Does not exist : string
      304 - Not handshaken
      311 - Already loged in : login
      312 - Wrong password
      313 - Not registered
      314 - Someone else already connected
      321 - Exist already
      341 - Already a friend
      342 - Already pending
      361 - Use DISCONNECT
      362 - Already in this status : status
      371 - Already in this channel
      372 - User disconnected
      373 - Already requested
      381 - Channel not joined
      391 - Not joined
      392 - Already calling
      401 - Unauthorized
      404 - Not found
      408 - Time-out
      418 - I'm a Teapot
      486 - Busy
      500 - Internal server error

  c - Client to client :
      14  - ACK
      15  - MICRO         : ON|OFF
      16  - SOUND         : ON|OFF
      17  - BYE

III - Details

  1  - CONNECT

    Connect client to server.

  2  - REGISTER

    Create a new account.

  3  - UPDATE

    Update user's data.

  4  - ADD

    Add a friend.

  5  - LIST_FRIENDS

    See list of contacts with their information.
    Possibility to display informations about one or more contact(s).

  6  - LIST_CHANNELS

    See list of channels that the user can connect with information.
    Possibility to display the information of one or more channels.

  7  - STATUS

    Send status change to the server.

  8  - QUIT

    Quit the server.

  9  - JOIN

    Ask to join a client or a channel.

  10 - CALL

    Ask for a new session.

  11 - SEND

    Send a text message to one or more user(s).

  12 - MICRO

    Turn on or off the microphone.

  13 - SOUND

    Turn on or off the sound.

  14 - ASK

    The server asks to client B if it accepts the add request from client A.
    This command is generated by the server after ADD(4) command.

  15 - REPLY

    The server sends to client A the answer of client B.
    This command is generated by the server after ASK(12) command.

  16 - ACK (start)

    Accept a new session.

  17 - CANCEL (ko)

    Decline new session. May be caused by timeout.

  18 - BYE

    Quit a session.